The '''{{lang|de|Bundesamt für Eich- und Vermessungswesen}}''' or '''BEV''' ([[German language|German]] for ''Federal Office of Metrology and Surveying'') is the body responsible for official surveying, geo-information and weights and measures ([[metrology]]) in [[Austria]]. It belongs to the ''{{lang|de|Bundesministerium für Wirtschaft, Familie und Jugend}}'' (Federal Ministry of the Economy, Family and Youth). Its headquarters is in [[Vienna]] and it has 67 branches spread across all the Austrian federal states.<ref>[http://www.bev.gv.at/portal/page?_pageid=713,1605147&_dad=portal&_schema=PORTAL ''Über das BEV''] at www.bev.gv.at. Accessed on 30 Dec 10.</ref>
==See also== *[[National mapping agency#List of national mapping agencies|(List of) national mapping agencies]]
