The following [[Outline (list)|outline]] is provided as an overview of and topical guide to South America.
'''[[South America]]''' is the southern continent of the two [[Americas]], situated entirely in the [[Western Hemisphere]] and mostly (about 3/4) in the [[Southern Hemisphere]]. It lies between the [[Pacific Ocean|Pacific]] and [[Atlantic Ocean|Atlantic]] oceans. The continent is culturally, [[ethnicity|ethnically]] and [[human race|racially]] diverse, home to [[Indigenous peoples of the Americas|indigenous peoples]] and to descendants of settlers from Europe, Africa and Asia. Due to its [[European colonization of the Americas|history of colonialism]] most South Americans speak [[Spanish language|Spanish]] or [[Portuguese language|Portuguese]], and its societies and states are commonly modeled after [[Western world|Western traditions]].
